cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the size of rewritings for conjunctive queries over OWL 2 QL ontologies, which is a topic related to database theory and logic. Therefore, cs.DB and cs.LO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses known lower bounds and separation results from circuit complexity, which suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses the size of rewritings for monotone Boolean functions, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR).
